In this article, President Barack Obama issues a memorandum stating that there is a sufficient supply of petroleum and petroleum products from countries other than Iran, allowing for a significant reduction in the volume of petroleum and petroleum products purchased from Iran by foreign financial institutions. The President mentions that this determination is based on factors such as global economic conditions, increased oil production by certain countries, and the level of spare capacity. He also mentions that he will continue to monitor the situation closely and authorizes the Secretary of State to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.